CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1966, pg. 13A reads: "Swing-Out - Last year's Rainbow Cotillion Queen, vivacious Lydia Bennett, a student at Howard University, and her dancing partner Richard Lewis, "swing-out" in one of the latest dancing fads. Music was provided by the Sell Thomas Quintett [sic], featuring Jules Thomas on organ..."
TitMainTitle: Lydia Bennett and Richard Lewis, dancing to the Sell Thomas Quintet, gathered in George Washington Hotel for Rainbow Cotillion, Washington, Pennsylvania
